cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on multi-agent scenarios and proposes a new state representation for deep multi-agent RL. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses deep reinforcement learning methods. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a new state representation using mean embeddings of distributions, which is a machine learning technique. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper evaluates the proposed representation on two well-known problems from the swarm literature (rendezvous and pursuit evasion), which are related to systems and control. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a new state representation for swarm systems, which can be applied to robotics.
